  "label": "Tomas Rellin",
  "description": "This individual is a broad-shouldered human laborer of early middle years, built for repeated heavy lifting and long hours of cart-work. Brown eyes sit beneath a heavy brow, and brown hair is kept in a shortknot that clears the face for work in dust and poor light. Bronze skin shows ingrained grime at the knuckles and forearms, with old, shallow abrasions that read as the ordinary record of warehouse handling. The voice and manner remain plain and workmanlike, marked by a steady patience suited to bonded stock, tally-calls, and hard deadlines.",
